      "entity_id": null,
      "paper_id": "paper_id",
      "text_span_id": "chemo_1",
      "text": "Studies utilizing selective estrogen receptor modulators (SERMs), including tamoxifen and raloxifene, and aromatase inhibitors (AIs) such as exemestane and anastrozole, have shown significant efficacy in lowering the risk of first breast cancer among high-risk individuals",
